The paper focuses on improving the reliability and latency of packet-based fronthauling for next-generation mobile networks, specifically for applications such as the Tactile Internet. This involves investigating the trade-off between reliability and latency, as well as considering the coexistence of different services in 5G networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.COMM (Communications and Networking), cs.AR (Architecture), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
